java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class GraphicsFitnessValue
extends javax.swing.JFrame

A graphical fitness value is a window that can plot fitness values throughout generations. It extends JFrame but uses own components (DComponents) to render and store anything that happens. This may definitely not be the best solution, it certainly was the easiest as most of it came from a different project.

The fitness values are plotted with a maximum scale. Different lines internally are identified only by color.

I'm not sure if we want to manage the lines in this class or not.. but we can always change that!

addFitnessValue

public void addFitnessValue(double fitnessValue,
                            int fromRound,
                            java.awt.Color color)
Adds a fitness value that the window this object represent should start drawing from (and to). We assume fromRound is the last round we want to represent in the window. In the future we might want to change this and make this optional (by choosing Program.MAX_EVOLUTIONS as the number of values to always represent.
